## Context
The PRD requires a thumbnail/poster generator UI for agents. The backend API will expose:
- `GET /thumbnails/templates` — returns `Array<{ id: string, name: string, description: string }>`
- `POST /thumbnails/properties/:propertyId/poster` — body: `{ templateId: string, headline?: string, keySpec?: string }` — returns `{ assets: Array<{ id: string, imageUrl: string, aspectRatio: string }> }`
- `GET /thumbnails/properties/:propertyId` — list existing thumbnails (already exists)

The web frontend uses: Next.js 14 App Router, React Query (`@tanstack/react-query`), Tailwind CSS, shadcn-style UI components. Components live in `apps/web/src/components/ui/`.
API calls use the `useApi()` hook: `const api = useApi(); await api.get('/thumbnails/...')` with `unwrap<T>()` helper.

## Your Job: Create the Poster Generator UI

### Part 1: Create the poster generator page

Create `apps/web/src/app/(agent)/properties/[id]/poster/page.tsx`:

This page should:
1. Load property details and existing thumbnails
2. Show a template selector (3 cards: Premium, Hot Property, Simple WhatsApp)
3. Show editable fields: headline (pre-filled from AI title), key spec text
4. "Generate Poster" button
5. After generation, show the 3 generated assets (16:9, 1:1, 9:16) with preview images
6. Download button for each
7. "Set as cover" button to use as smart link preview

### Part 2: Create PosterGenerator component

Create `apps/web/src/components/PosterGenerator.tsx`:

A reusable client component that:
```typescript
interface PosterGeneratorProps {
  propertyId: string;
  propertyTitle: string;
  coverImageUrl?: string;
}

// State:
// - selectedTemplate: string ('premium')
// - headline: string (default: propertyTitle)
// - keySpec: string
// - generatedAssets: Array<{ id: string, imageUrl: string, aspectRatio: string }>
// - isGenerating: boolean

// Uses useApi() and useMutation for POST /thumbnails/properties/:propertyId/poster
```

Layout:
- Top: Template selector — 3 cards side by side, each showing template name + short description
  - Premium: "Professional layout with pricing and contact details"
  - Hot Property: "Bold red banner for urgent or high-demand listings"  
  - Simple WhatsApp: "Clean, minimal design optimized for WhatsApp status"
- Middle: Editable fields
  - Headline input (text, max 80 chars)
  - Key spec input (text, max 60 chars, placeholder: "3 BHK · 1200 sqft · East Facing")
- Bottom: Generate button (orange, full width) then results grid

After generation:
- Show 3 images in a responsive grid with aspect-ratio labels
- Each image card: preview img, aspect ratio badge, download button
- "Set as cover" button on the 16:9 one

### Part 3: Add navigation link

In the property detail page (likely at `apps/web/src/app/(agent)/properties/[id]/page.tsx`), add a "Generate Poster" button/link that navigates to the poster page. Check the existing property detail page first — use `read_file` to find it.

If the property detail page doesn't exist at that exact path, search for it with `file_search` or `grep_files` for "properties" in the web src.

### Styling
- Use Tailwind classes
- Orange primary: bg-orange-500, text-orange-600, border-orange-200
- Cards: rounded-lg border bg-white p-4
- Use the existing Card/CardContent components from @/components/ui/card
- Use the existing Button component from @/components/ui/button
- Use the existing Input and Label from @/components/ui/input and @/components/ui/label
- Toast notifications via useToast() hook

### Edge cases
- Loading state: show skeleton/spinner while templates load
- Empty state: "No cover photo — upload photos first" if no cover
- Error state: toast on generation failure
- Disabled state: disable Generate button while generating

### API types
```typescript
interface PosterTemplate {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  description: string;
}

interface GeneratedAsset {
  id: string;
  imageUrl: string;
  aspectRatio: string;
}

interface PosterGenerateResponse {
  assets: GeneratedAsset[];
}
```

